---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';
---

<BaseLayout title="Bio" description="About me and what I work on" locale="en">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Bio</h1>
	<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">{site.bioEn}</p>

	<section class="mt-10 grid gap-4">
		<div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900/40">
			<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">What I do</h2>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
				<li>End-to-end automation with Playwright (Python/TS), with a strong focus on reliability</li>
				<li>Robot Framework at scale: keyword design, layering, reusable resources, and maintainability</li>
				<li>CI quality & speed: reduce flaky tests, shorten feedback loops, improve signal-to-noise</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900/40">
			<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">What you can expect</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
				I prefer pragmatic engineering: clean architecture, readable tests, stable pipelines, and a focus on long-term total cost.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
